== Project Overview

The Greenhouse Management System (GMS) is a multi-layered IoT platform for automated environmental monitoring and control. It spans five core subsystems: Sensor Acquisition & Environmental Monitoring, Local Automation Engine, Cloud Backend, Web Dashboard & User Interface, and a Cybersecurity layer, all coordinated through a 4-layer architecture (Hardware / Edge / Cloud / Client) running on a dual-core STM32H747 edge controller augmented by a Mini PC edge gateway and cloud AI agent service.

