== Individual Responsibilities

- ** Victoria Mutruc - Frontend Developer**
  - Design and implement all web dashboard UI components: sensor dashboard, alert panel, irrigation control panel, schedule manager, threshold configuration UI, historical trend view, resource summary panel, and multi-site dashboard
  - Integrate WebSocket/SSE push for real-time alert banners (5 s) and sensor data refresh (10 s)
  - Implement JWT login flow with role-based operator gates on the frontend
  - Implement CSV/XLSX data export (90-day window, 5 mandatory fields)
  - Ensure mobile-first rendering, alert prioritisation display, and data freshness indication
  - Connect all UI views to the Cloud REST API Gateway via HTTPS
  - Co-maintain Confluence documentation, traceability tables, and team responsibilities pages alongside Daria

- ** Adrian Vremere - Hardware Developer**
  - Co-implement the Sensor Acquisition & Environmental Monitoring System alongside Maxim: RS-485/SHT10/UART hardware interface, SensorPoller, DataValidator, ThresholdEvaluator, AlertClassifier, and SensorFaultMonitor
  - Co-implement the Local Automation Engine alongside Maxim: AutomationDecisionEngine, IrrigationController, ClimateController, ScheduleExecutor, OfflineBufferManager, ResourceLogger, and ActuatorSafetyInterlock
  - Co-define the 4-layer system architecture (Hardware/Edge/Cloud/Client) with SR group mapping and architectural decision rationale
  - Co-design the Mini PC Edge Gateway architecture: LocalMQTTBroker, WANMQTTClient, DecisionEngine, ScheduleExecutor, AIDecisionCache, ConfigStore, OfflineBufferManager
  - Collaborate on edge hardware validation and system integration testing

- ** Maxim Alexei - Hardware / Backend Developer**
  - Co-implement the Sensor Acquisition & Environmental Monitoring System alongside Adrian: RS-485/SHT10/UART hardware interface, SensorPoller, DataValidator, ThresholdEvaluator, AlertClassifier, and SensorFaultMonitor
  - Co-implement the Local Automation Engine alongside Adrian: GPIO/relay actuation logic (30 s automatic / 10 s manual modes), PID anti-windup, actuator conflict resolution, and 72-hour offline autonomy
  - Build the non-blocking MQTT payload serialisation pipeline to the Cortex-M4 MQTT client and offline buffer feed to the OfflineBufferManager
  - Co-define the 4-layer system architecture (Hardware/Edge/Cloud/Client) with SR group mapping and architectural decision rationale
  - Co-design the Mini PC Edge Gateway architecture: LocalMQTTBroker, WANMQTTClient, DecisionEngine, ScheduleExecutor, AIDecisionCache, ConfigStore, OfflineBufferManager
  - Collaborate on system integration and edge hardware validation

- ** Daniel Cojocaru - Backend Developer**
  - Co-build the Cloud Backend System alongside Daria: MQTT broker, data ingestion service, alert evaluation service, REST API gateway, and analytics service
  - Implement resource usage logging to Cloud Time-Series DB via MQTT and batch-flush buffered records on reconnect
  - Co-implement the Cybersecurity System: TLS 1.2+ X.509 mTLS termination, JWT + RBAC request guard, append-only audit logger, offline edge auth module, certificate store, and user account manager
  - Lead the AI Agent Service: sensor data consumer, AI decision model, command issuer, and tenant scope filter
  - Collaborate on system integration testing across backend layers

- ** Daria Rateeva - Backend Developer**
  - Co-build the Cloud Backend System alongside Daniel: notification dispatcher (Twilio/FCM), AuthNAuthZService, InfluxDB/TimescaleDB integration with 90-day retention, and CLOUDSYNC-IF batch-flush on reconnect
  - Implement CLOUDNOTIF-IF: Twilio/FCM push/SMS notification gateway (30 s dispatch after 60 s persist)
  - Co-implement the Cybersecurity System: JWT + RBAC via AuthNAuthZService, append-only audit logger, certificate store, and user account manager
  - Support system integration testing across cloud backend layers
  - Co-maintain Confluence documentation, traceability tables, and team responsibilities pages alongside Victoria
